Here is a table of the first 5 presidents of the United States with their names, age when they started office, year they started office, and number of years they served:

| President | Name | Age When Started Office | Year Started Office | Number of Years Served |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| George Washington | George Washington | 56 | 1789 | 8 |
| John Adams | John Adams | 55 | 1797 | 8 |
| Thomas Jefferson | Thomas Jefferson | 43 | 1801 | 12 |
| James Madison | James Madison | 44 | 1809 | 12 |
| James Monroe | James Monroe | 51 | 1817 | 8 |

Note: This table only includes the first 5 presidents of the United States. There were a total of 44 presidents in all.
